**Primitive-first rule:** Every component that CAN be composed from `Box`, `Pressable`, `Text`, `NavIcon` MUST be. Exceptions: Gluestack overlay compounds (Modal, Tooltip, AlertDialog) manage DOM portals; HTML input wrappers (DatePicker, ColorPicker, etc.) wrap native elements for semantic/accessibility reasons.

**Rule:** When adding a new palette entry, prefer `Pressable`/`Box`/`Text`/`NavIcon` primitives. Use Gluestack compound components only when no primitive equivalent exists. All new Gluestack compound sub-components need `REQUIRED_PARENT` / `ALLOWED_CHILDREN` entries in `_store.ts`.

