## Showcase Nodes — Every Node Must Have an `id` (use `ensureIds`)

**Problem:** Inner children of showcase cards (e.g. "John Doe" text inside a Profile Card) cannot be clicked/selected in the builder. They appear invisible to the hit-test — clicking them selects the outer card wrapper instead.

**Root cause:** The SDUI renderer only stamps `data-builder-id` on nodes that have an explicit `id` field (see `renderer.tsx` line `if (node.id)`). Inline child objects written without `id: uid()` never get `data-builder-id`, so `hitTest`'s `closest('[data-builder-id]')` walk falls back to the nearest ancestor that has one — typically the outer container.

**Fix:** Add a recursive `ensureIds` helper in `_showcase.ts` and apply it to the root nodes before export:

```ts
function ensureIds(node: SDUINode): SDUINode {
  return {
    ...node,
    id: node.id ?? uid(),
    children: node.children?.map(ensureIds),
  };
}

// At the bottom:
export const showcaseNodes: SDUINode[] = showcaseRaw.map(ensureIds);
```

**Rule:** Any time you add nodes to the showcase (or any builder page config) that are defined inline without `id` fields, wrap the root array with `ensureIds`. Never export showcase nodes directly without this pass — inner nodes without `id` are permanently unselectable in the builder.

