## Showcase / Preview — Grid Layout Must Have `w-full`

**Problem:** The showcase `row()` grid (`grid grid-cols-3 gap-6 items-start`) renders correctly in the builder canvas but shows the wrong number of columns in the preview tab.

**Root cause:** NativeWind's `Box` → React Native `View` does **not** auto-expand to fill its parent. Without `w-full`, the grid container collapses to its content size. CSS `grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr)` computes `1fr` relative to the container's actual width — if the container is content-sized, each `1fr` equals one item's natural width, letting many items pack per row instead of exactly 3.

In the builder canvas the page frame has a fixed pixel `width` set via inline style, which forces children to stretch. In the preview tab there is no such frame, so the collapsed grid becomes visible.

**Fix:**
1. Add `w-full` to every grid container in `_showcase.ts` `row()`:
   ```ts
   props: { className: 'grid grid-cols-3 gap-6 items-start w-full' }
   ```
2. Add `grid-cols-*` to the Tailwind safelist in `tailwind.config.js`:
   ```js
   { pattern: /^grid-cols-(\d+)$/ },
   { pattern: /^grid-rows-(\d+)$/ },
   { pattern: /^col-span-(\d+)$/ },
   { pattern: /^row-span-(\d+)$/ },
   ```

**Rule:** Every `grid` container in the showcase (and in any SDUI screen) must include `w-full`. Without it, the grid will look correct only when the parent has an explicit fixed width (like the builder canvas frame), and will break in the actual preview/page context.

