## Critical Bug Fixes (Do Not Repeat)

### 1. Button disappears when any className is added

**Root cause:** `components/ui/button/index.tsx` used `hasCustomClassName(className)` — any non-empty className (even `py-0 px-0` from padding) triggered `effectiveAction = 'custom'` → `bg-transparent`.

**Fix:** Only switch to `'custom'` action when className contains a `bg-*` token:
```tsx
const hasBg = useCustom && /\bbg-/.test(className!);
const effectiveAction = hasBg ? 'custom' : action;
```
**Rule:** Adding padding, margin, border-radius, opacity, or any non-color class to a Button must NOT override its background color.

---

### 2. Opacity uses inline `style.opacity`, never `opacity-N` class

**Root cause:** NativeWind does not compile dynamically applied `opacity-95`, `opacity-50` etc. (they're not in the source at build time).

**Fix:** Store opacity as `style.opacity` (decimal 0–1). The slider `min=5` prevents accidental 0%. At 100%, `style.opacity` is removed entirely.

**Rule:** Never add `opacity-N` classes dynamically. Always use `patchStyle({ opacity: String(val/100) })`.

---

### 3. Rotation uses inline `style.transform`, never `rotate-[Ndeg]` class

**Root cause:** Same NativeWind dynamic class compilation issue.

**Fix:** Store rotation as `style.transform = rotate(Ndeg)`.

**Rule:** Never add `rotate-[...]` classes dynamically. Use `patchStyle({ transform: \`rotate(\${deg}deg)\` })`.

---

### 3b. Overlay ring / X/Y/W/H lag during panel edits (rotation, opacity, etc.)

**Root cause 1 (ring lag):** The overlay's `useLayoutEffect` and `selectedRects` useMemo depended only on `tick` (RAF loop). The RAF loop stops 200 ms after the last canvas hover/scroll. When the user is only clicking the panel, `tick` is frozen → ring doesn't reposition to match the newly rotated element.

**Fix:** Added `pageNodes` to both `useLayoutEffect([tick, pageNodes])` and `selectedRects` useMemo deps in `_overlay.tsx`. Every `patchProp` call creates a new `pageNodes` reference, triggering the layout effect before paint.

**Root cause 2 (X/Y/W/H lag):** `domMetrics` was a `useMemo` that ran during the render phase (before React committed the new style to DOM). It read stale BCR values. Also, `patchStyle` debounces the Zustand commit by 80 ms, so during rapid pressing the `useLayoutEffect([store.pageNodes])` that recomputes domMetrics fires at most once per 80 ms.

**Fix 1:** Converted `domMetrics` from `useMemo` to `useState` driven by `useLayoutEffect` (after commit → correct BCR).

**Fix 2:** Inside `patchStyle`, right after the direct DOM mutation (step 1), read `getBoundingClientRect()` and imperatively set `.value` on the `input-pos-x/y/w/h` DOM inputs. This gives frame-perfect X/Y/W/H updates with zero React re-renders — same frame as the component rotation.

**Rule:** Any panel control that produces a direct DOM mutation via `patchStyle` step 1 must also update any read-only DOM metrics displays imperatively (via `querySelector + inp.value = ...`) in the same synchronous call, NOT via React state. React state (domMetrics) is the fallback for zoom changes, node selection changes, and the post-debounce settle render.

---

### 4. Colors use inline `style.backgroundColor / color / borderColor`

**Root cause:** NativeWind doesn't reliably compile arbitrary `bg-[#hex]` classes set dynamically at runtime.

**Fix:** All color picker changes use `patchStyle({ backgroundColor: hex })`, `patchStyle({ color: hex })`, `patchStyle({ borderColor: hex })`.

---

### 5. Flip H/V toggle-off didn't work (`\b` regex bug)

**Root cause:** `removeTwToken(cls, '-scale-x-')` generated regex `\b-scale-x-\S*`. The `\b` (word boundary) never fires before `-` (non-word char), so `-scale-x-100` could never be removed.

**Fix:** `removeTwToken` detects when prefix starts with a non-word char and uses `(?:^|\s)` boundary instead:
```ts
if (/^\w/.test(prefix)) {
  return className.replace(new RegExp(`\\b${escaped}\\S*`, 'g'), '')...
}
return className.replace(new RegExp(`(?:^|\\s)${escaped}\\S*`, 'g'), ' ')...
```
**Rule:** Any Tailwind utility starting with `-` (negated scale, negated rotate) requires the `(?:^|\s)` boundary, not `\b`.

---

### 6. Border radius: per-corner tokens vs global tokens

**Root cause:** The old `applyBorderRadius` emitted `rounded-lg rounded-none rounded-none rounded-none` (all global, last one wins → all corners = none). `expandBorderRadius` returned per-corner tokens like `rounded-tl-lg` which don't match any `ROUNDED_TOKENS` select option.

**Fix:**
- `expandBorderRadius`: parse per-corner tokens via regex `\brounded-tl(?:-\S+)?`, convert back to global format (`rounded-tl-lg` → `rounded-lg`) for select display.
- `applyBorderRadius`: when corners differ, emit per-corner tokens (`rounded-tl-lg rounded-tr-none…`); when equal, emit single global token.
- Helper `globalToCornerToken('rounded-lg', 'tl')` → `'rounded-tl-lg'`.

**Rule:** Never concatenate four global `rounded-*` tokens for mixed corners. Always convert to `rounded-{corner}-{size}`.

---

### 7. CONTAINER_TYPES Must Stay in Sync Across Three Files

**Root cause:** `CONTAINER_TYPES` in `_canvas.tsx` and `LAYER_CONTAINER_TYPES` in `_panel-left.tsx` only contained 8 types (`Box`, `VStack`, `HStack`, `ScrollView`, `View`, `Card`, `SafeAreaView`, `Pressable`). Any type NOT in this set is treated as a leaf — you cannot drop children into it when it's empty (the `children.length > 0` fallback only helps non-empty containers).

**Impact:** `Center`, `Grid`, `GridItem`, and all Gluestack compound containers were non-droppable when first placed on the canvas.

**Fix:** All three sets must include the **same container types**:
- `_canvas.tsx` → `CONTAINER_TYPES` (controls drag-over hit logic)
- `_panel-left.tsx` → `LAYER_CONTAINER_TYPES` (controls layers-panel expand icon)
- `_panel-right.tsx` → `isContainer` array (controls Auto Layout design panel section)

**Rule:** Whenever you add a new container component to the palette, add its `type` string to all three locations. The canonical list is in `_panel-right.tsx`'s `isContainer` array.

---

### 8. defaultNode className Must Include All Implicit Style Tokens

**Root cause:** The right panel reads layout/alignment tokens (`flex-row`, `flex-col`, `items-*`, `justify-*`) exclusively from `props.className`. Gluestack compound components (Center, VStack, HStack, etc.) apply these tokens internally via their `tva` base styles — NOT from `props.className`. So when a component is freshly dropped, the panel shows no direction selected and no alignment cell highlighted even though the component visually centers/stacks correctly.

**Fix:** Always include all layout-defining tokens explicitly in `defaultNode.props.className`:
- `Center` → `flex flex-col items-center justify-center`
- `VStack` → `flex flex-col`
- `HStack` → `flex flex-row`
- Any other container with an implicit flex direction or alignment → add those tokens to `className`

**Rule:** If a component has implicit `flex-*`, `items-*`, or `justify-*` built into its component style, mirror those tokens in `defaultNode.className` so the right panel reflects the actual visual behavior immediately on drop.

---

### 9. Padding / Margin / Gap — exact pixel values via inline style

**Root cause:** Using Tailwind spacing scale (`pxToSpacingScale`) forced values to snap to 2px increments. Input `1` → rounded to `0` → no margin. Input `3` → `mx-0.5` (not compiled in older safelist).

**Fix:** All three use `patchStyle` with direct CSS properties:
- Padding: `style.paddingLeft/Right/Top/Bottom`
- Margin: `style.marginLeft/Right/Top/Bottom`
- Gap: `style.gap`

**Rule:** Never use `patchCls(applyPadding/applyMargin/pxToTw)` for user-entered spacing values in the builder. Use `patchStyle` with exact `px` strings so any value the user types is applied exactly.

---

### 8. Lifecycle triggers must NOT become DOM event props

**Problem:** `action-binding.ts` `bindEventHandler` has a catch-all `else` that converts any unrecognised trigger name to a camelCase prop (e.g. `created` → `onCreated`). React logs "Unknown event handler property `onCreated`" and silently drops it. The handler never fires.

**Triggers affected:** `created`, `mounted`, `submitValidationError` — these are lifecycle/engine events, not DOM events.

**Fix:** Added `LIFECYCLE_TRIGGERS` set in `action-binding.ts`. Early return at the top of `bindEventHandler` when `LIFECYCLE_TRIGGERS.has(event)`.

```ts
const LIFECYCLE_TRIGGERS = new Set(['created', 'mounted', 'submitValidationError']);
// inside bindEventHandler:
if (LIFECYCLE_TRIGGERS.has(event)) return;
```

**Rule:** Any new trigger that is not a DOM event must be added to `LIFECYCLE_TRIGGERS` in `action-binding.ts`.

---

### 9. `navigateTo` step must use `type:'navigate'`, not `action:'navigate'`

**Problem:** `stepToSdui` for `navigateTo` returned `{ action: 'navigate', payload: { path } }`. In `runOne`, `actionsConfig['navigate']` is `undefined` (no named action). `dispatchToHandler(undefined, ...)` throws `TypeError: Cannot read properties of undefined (reading 'type')` — crashing the page.

**Fix:** Changed `stepToSdui` `navigateTo` case to return `{ type: 'navigate', path, routeConfig, linkType, externalUrl, newTab }`. The `runOne` fallback (`'type' in action`) catches this and dispatches to `ACTION_HANDLERS['navigate']` correctly.

```ts
// workflow-steps-handler.ts
case 'navigateTo':
  if (cfg.queryParams) { return { type: 'navigateWithQuery', ... }; }
  return { type: 'navigate', path: cfg.path, routeConfig: cfg.routeConfig, ... };
```

Also added `if (!actionDef) return false;` guard at the top of `dispatchToHandler` in `actions/handlers/index.ts` for defensive safety.

**Rule:** `stepToSdui` must always return objects with `type:` (not `action:`). Actions keyed by name live in actionsConfig and are resolved by the outer `runOne` — they must not be embedded as action refs inside `stepToSdui`.

---

### 8. `pxToSpacingScale` ties round UP

When a px value is equally distant between two scale values (e.g. `1` ties between `0` and `2`), round UP:
```ts
.reduce((a, b) => Math.abs(b - px) <= Math.abs(a - px) ? b : a);
```
Previously used `<` which always rounded down → `1` → `0` → no spacing.

---

## `_tw-utils.ts` — Key Utilities

### `removeTwToken(className, prefix)`
Removes all tokens matching prefix. Uses `\b` for word-char prefixes (`p-`, `gap-`, `rounded-`). Uses `(?:^|\s)` for non-word-char prefixes (`-scale-x-`, `-rotate-`).

### `replaceTwToken(className, prefix, newToken)`
Replaces the first matching token, or appends if none found. Uses `(?:^|\s)` boundary with space-preserving replacement.

### `parseTwToken(className, prefix)`
Returns the first token matching `\b{prefix}\S*`, or `null`.

### `expandPadding / expandBorderRadius / expandMargin`
Parse className into structured px/token values for display in inputs. These are ONLY used for reading initial values (display). Writing always uses `patchStyle`.

### `applyAlignment(className, cellIdx)`
Maps 0–8 cell index → `items-*` + `justify-*` classes. Used by the 9-cell grid.

### `globalToCornerToken(global, corner)`
`'rounded-lg'` + `'tl'` → `'rounded-tl-lg'`. Used in `applyBorderRadius` for mixed-corner case.

---

## Tailwind Safelist (`tailwind.config.js`)

All dynamically applied builder classes must be in the safelist. Current coverage:
- Spacing: `p/px/py/pt/pr/pb/pl-{scale}` (includes decimals like `1.5`)
- Margin: `m/mx/my/mt/mr/mb/ml-{scale|auto}` (includes decimals)
- Gap, W, H, max-w, opacity, rounded, text-*, font-*, leading, tracking
- Flex: direction, items, justify, wrap
- Rotate (including negated and arbitrary): `-?rotate-(N|[...])`, `-?scale-x/y-*`
- Position: `static/relative/absolute/fixed/sticky`
- Z-index: `z-0/10/20/30/40/50/auto`
- Cursor, display, overflow, text-align, text-decoration, text-transform, self-*

**Rule:** Any new class dynamically applied by the builder must be added to the safelist OR stored as an inline style property.

---

## E2E Tests

Tests use `window.__builderStore` (exposed at **module level** in `_store.ts`, NOT in a `useEffect`) to read/write Zustand state directly. Available as soon as the JS bundle loads, before React hydration completes.

**`gotoBuilder` pattern:**
```ts
async function gotoBuilder(page: Page) {
  await page.goto('/dev/builder');
  await page.waitForSelector('[data-builder-page-frame]', { timeout: 30_000 });
  await page.waitForSelector('[data-testid="tab-components"]', { timeout: 15_000 });
  await page.waitForFunction(
    () => !!(window as unknown as Record<string, unknown>).__builderStore,
    { timeout: 20_000, polling: 100 }
  );
}
```

**`injectNodes` pattern** (preferred over drag-and-drop):
```ts
async function injectNodes(page: Page, nodes: unknown[]) {
  await page.evaluate((n) => {
    (window as unknown as Record<string, { getState: () => { _setPageNodes: (n: unknown[]) => void } }>)
      .__builderStore.getState()._setPageNodes(n);
  }, nodes);
  // ALL nodes must have `id` for data-builder-id to be set
  await page.waitForSelector(`[data-builder-id="${(nodes[0] as {id: string}).id}"]`, { timeout: 8_000 });
}
```

**Key helpers:**
- `gotoBuilder(page)` — navigate to `/dev/builder`, wait for frame + tabs + store
- `injectNodes(page, nodes)` — set page nodes directly via store (bypasses flaky drag-and-drop)
- `selectViaLayers(page)` — click Layers tab → first layer-row → Design tab
- `getNodeClassName(page, nodeId)` — reads `node.props.className` from store
- `getNodeStyle(page, nodeId)` — reads `node.props.style` from store
- `scrollTo(page, testId)` — scrolls element into view inside overflow panel container

**`sharedPage` + `resetBuilder` pattern** (mandatory for ALL spec files — navigate once, reset between tests):

```ts
import { test, expect, Page, Browser } from '@playwright/test';

let sharedPage: Page;

async function resetBuilder(p: Page) {
  await p.evaluate(() => {
    const store = (window as unknown as Record<string, { getState: () => Record<string, unknown> }>).__builderStore?.getState();
    if (!store) return;
    (store._setPageNodes as (n: unknown[]) => void)([]);
    if (typeof store.setSelectedIds === 'function') (store.setSelectedIds as (ids: string[]) => void)([]);
    if (typeof store.setZoom === 'function') (store.setZoom as (z: number) => void)(1);
  });
  await p.waitForFunction(
    () => document.querySelectorAll('[data-builder-id]').length === 0,
    { timeout: 5_000 }
  );
}

// File-level (outside any describe) — opens ONE page for the entire file
test.beforeAll(async ({ browser }: { browser: Browser }) => {
  sharedPage = await browser.newPage();
  await gotoBuilder(sharedPage);
});
test.afterAll(async () => { await sharedPage?.close(); });
test.beforeEach(async () => { await resetBuilder(sharedPage); }); // only if no describe-level beforeEach

// Inside a describe block — same pattern:
test.describe('My Group', () => {
  test.beforeEach(async () => { await resetBuilder(sharedPage); });
  test('my test', async () => {
    const page = sharedPage; // alias so existing code works unchanged
    // ...
  });
});
```

**Why `resetBuilder` instead of `gotoBuilder`:** Full page navigation costs 5–15s per test. `resetBuilder` clears nodes/selection/zoom via the store in <100ms. Always prefer `resetBuilder` in `beforeEach`; reserve `gotoBuilder` only for cases that require a fresh undo history (e.g. History/Undo tests in `builder.spec.ts`).

**History tests exception:** `_setPageNodes([])` does NOT clear the undo stack. Tests that test undo/redo must use `gotoBuilder(page)` (the Playwright fixture page, not `sharedPage`) so each gets a clean history:
```ts
test.describe('History (Undo / Redo)', () => {
  // No beforeEach here — each test uses its own page fixture
  test('undo after drop removes the node', async ({ page }) => {
    await gotoBuilder(page); // fresh page = clean history
    // ...
  });
});
```

**Test series:**
- `BP-00`–`BP-44` (in `panel-interactive.spec.ts`): Pressable-based button, all right-panel controls. Replaces old `button-panel.spec.ts` (deleted).
- `PI-01`–`PI-03`: Content section for Pressable with Text children.
- `PF-01`–`PF-16` (in `panel-form.spec.ts`): Input, Textarea, Checkbox, Toggle.
- `PD-01`–`PD-11` (in `panel-display.spec.ts`): Heading, Badge, Avatar.
- `PM-01`–`PM-10` (in `panel-media.spec.ts`): NextImage (placeholder, resize, src), NavIcon (size/color), Icon Tap.
- `T1`–`T11`: Dimension, rotate, NumberInput, moveNode, drop zone, opacity.
- `U1`–`U14`: Alignment, flip, auto layout, gap, clip, stroke, typography, DOM visual update.
- `V1`–`V8`: Color pickers, visibility with gap, section visibility per node type, self-alignment.
- `DI-01`–`DI-04`: Drop indicator direction — vertical line for row/HStack, horizontal for column.
- `Fix-DropLine-1/2`: Drop line not shown over dragged node, moveNode correct index placement.

**Selection in E2E — use Layers panel, not canvas click:**
Canvas click-to-select can be unreliable in Playwright/headless — the capture overlay's `onPointerDown` may not fire. For tests that need a node selected, use the Layers panel instead:
```ts
await page.getByTestId('tab-layers').click();
await page.getByTestId('layer-row').first().click();
```

**Injected nodes must have `id` fields:** Without `id`, the renderer does not set `data-builder-id`, making `waitForSelector('[data-builder-id="..."]')` time out.

**Timeout:** Global Playwright timeout is `30_000`ms (fail fast). The dev server must be running on port 3001 (`npx next dev -p 3001`). The `webServer` startup timeout is `60_000`ms. Workers are set to `10` (matching CPU count) so all 12 spec files run simultaneously.

