## Theme Panel + FigmaColorPicker

### ThemePanel (`_theme-panel.tsx`)

A collapsible panel rendered in the "Theme" tab of the left panel. Sections:
- **Global Colors** — semantic CSS vars: `background`, `foreground`, `primary`, `secondary`, `muted`, `accent`, `destructive`, `border`, `ring`
- **Section Colors** — grouped by section (Header, Footer, Hero, Content, Shop); each color editable live
- **Typography** — heading/body font pickers (Google Fonts injected on-demand via `<link>` into `document.head`)
- **Border Radius** — preset tiles that write to `--radius` CSS var

All changes go through `patchTheme(cssVar, value)` in `_store.ts`, which:
1. Calls `document.documentElement.style.setProperty(`--${cssVar}`, value)` for live canvas update
2. Stores the override in `themeOverrides: Record<string, string>` (Zustand)

`resetTheme()` removes all `setProperty` overrides and clears `themeOverrides`.

**Rule:** Font changes also use `patchTheme('font-heading', fontValue)`. Google Fonts are injected via a `<link>` element only if the URL is not already in the document head.

---

### FigmaColorPicker (`_color-picker.tsx`)

Replaces the old `ColorInput` component in the Design tab (Fill, Stroke, Typography sections).

**Props:**
```typescript
interface FigmaColorPickerProps {
  value: string;           // current hex
  onChange: (hex: string) => void;
  label?: string;          // "Background", "Color", etc.
  testId?: string;
}
```

**Popover layout:**
1. **Theme Colors** — 6-column swatch grid (Global: Primary, Secondary, Muted, etc.)
2. **Section Colors** — 6-column swatch grid (Header bg, Footer bg, Shop btn, etc.)
3. **Custom** — native `<input type="color">` + hex text field

**Swatch behavior:** Clicking a swatch resolves the CSS variable via `getComputedStyle(document.documentElement).getPropertyValue(`--${cssVar}`)` to the current hex (respecting any live `themeOverrides`), then calls `onChange(hex)`. The resolved hex is stored as an inline style value — consistent with the existing builder pattern (colors always stored as hex strings, never as CSS var references).

**Popover close:** `mousedown` handler on `document`; popover stays open during `<input type="color">` interactions.

**Rule:** Never store `var(--primary)` etc. as inline style values — always resolve to hex before calling `onChange`. The rest of the builder pipeline (serialize → preview → SDUI engine) handles hex only.

**Rule:** `FigmaColorPicker` is used for Fill (background), Stroke (border), and Typography (text color) in `_panel-right.tsx`. The old `ColorInput` function remains in `_panel-right.tsx` only as a backup but is no longer rendered.

