## §38 Formula Editor — Chips, Auto-chip, Undo/Redo, Copy/Cut/Paste

### Chip building

Three chip builders live at the top of `_formula-editor.tsx`:

| Builder | Usage | Colour |
|---|---|---|
| `buildChipSpan(formula, label, type)` | collection/variable paths | blue `#1d4ed8` / green `#15803d` |
| `buildOperatorChip(label, insert, category)` | operators and punctuation | neutral gray `#374151` |
| `buildFunctionChip(fnName)` | known function names | same gray as operators |

All chips use `padding:2px 4px`, `border-radius:5px`, `margin:0 1px`, `font-size:11px`, `contentEditable="false"`. **No** `user-select:none` — chips must be visually selectable via Cmd+A.

`data-type` attribute: `"collection"`, `"variable"`, `"operator"`, `"function"`.
`data-formula` attribute: the raw formula string the chip represents (used by `serializeEditor`).

For function chips, `data-formula` is the function **name only** (e.g. `ifEmpty`), not `ifEmpty(` — inserting the `(` chip separately prevents duplicate `((` on copy.

### Auto-chip on typing (`rechipCurrentTextNode`)

Called from `onInput`. Scans the current text node using `AUTO_CHIP_RE` (longest-match-first alternation):
```
/===|!==|>=|<=|&&|\|\||\(|\)|,|\+|\*|\/|%|-|>|</g
```
Converts matched tokens to `buildOperatorChip` nodes. **Exception:** when `(` is matched, checks if the text immediately before it is a known function name (`FN_NAME_SUFFIX_RE`) — if so, chips the function name first, then chips `(`.

**Key constraint:** `AUTO_CHIP_RE` fires per-keystroke. Multi-char operators like `>=` do NOT auto-chip from keystrokes (the `>` is chipped first before `=` is typed). To get a `>=` chip, paste the string with surrounding spaces ` >= ` so `OP_TOKEN_RE` can match the full insert form.

### Undo/Redo history

Custom history stack via `historyRef` / `historyIdxRef`. Rules:
- When `rechipCurrentTextNode` returns `true` (chip was created), call `pushHistory` **immediately** (not debounced) so each chip is its own undo step.
- When plain text is typed, use `pushHistoryDebounced` (400ms) to group strokes.
- In `handleKeyDown` for Cmd+Z / Cmd+Shift+Z, **cancel the pending debounce timer** (`clearTimeout(historyTimerRef.current)`) before executing undo/redo to prevent stale snapshots from corrupting the redo stack.

### Copy / Cut / Paste

- **Copy** (`handleCopy`): serialises the selected fragment via `serializeRangeFromEditor` to a raw formula string and writes to clipboard. HTML chips are NOT copied.
- **Cut** (`handleCut`): same as copy + deletes the selected content. Calls `normalizeEditorContent` after deletion.
- **Paste** (`handlePaste`): reads plain text, conditionally calls `restoreCaret()` (only when no live selection), then `insertPastedFormulaAtCaret`. Calls `normalizeEditorContent` after insertion to clean up any stray blocks.

`restoreCaret()` is guarded: it only restores the saved range when the editor is **not** focused and has no active selection, to avoid overwriting a live Cmd+A selection.

### Normalisation (`normalizeEditorContent`)

Called on `onInput`, after paste, and after cut. Two passes:
1. **Pass 1** — removes stray `<br>` and unwraps browser-injected `<div>`/`<p>` blocks (caused by backspace next to non-editable chips).
2. **Pass 2** — inserts a Zero-Width Space (`\u200b`) between every pair of directly adjacent non-editable chips to give the browser a stable cursor anchor.

`\u200b` is stripped during serialisation (`serializeEditor`, `serializeRangeFromEditor`).

### Data tab chip colours

Collection header pills (`data-testid="fe-collection-pill-*"`) and `DataTreeNode` field-name buttons must use the same colours as collection chips in the editor:
- Background: `#1d4ed8` (hover: `#2563eb`)
- Text: `#bfdbfe`
- Border: `1px solid #2563eb`
- Padding: `2px 4px`
- Font-size: `11px`, `font-weight:600`, `font-family:monospace`

This gives users visual continuity between what they click in the tree and what they see as chips in the formula input.

### Layout — Current value section

"Current value" and "Expected" labels are rendered as **separate column rows** (not inline), each with its preview box spanning full width:

```tsx
<div style={{ display: 'flex', flexDirection: 'column', gap: 4 }}>
  {/* Row 1 — Current value (full width) */}
  <div style={{ display: 'flex', flexDirection: 'column', gap: 2 }}>
    <span>Current value</span>
    <div style={{ width: '100%' }}>...</div>
  </div>
  {/* Row 2 — Expected (only when set) */}
  {(hint || expectedType !== 'any') && (
    <div style={{ display: 'flex', flexDirection: 'column', gap: 2 }}>
      <span>Expected</span>
      <div style={{ width: '100%' }}>...</div>
    </div>
  )}
</div>
```

### E2E test file

`e2e/builder-formula-chips.spec.ts` — Groups M–T (FE-M01 to FE-T05, 40 tests):

| Group | What is tested |
|---|---|
| M | Auto-chip on typing each operator (40 tests, one per operator) |
| N | Function auto-chip when `(` follows a known function name |
| O | Undo/redo history: per-chip steps, stale-debounce fix, round-trip |
| P | Copy/cut/paste: clipboard content, selection replace, no new-lines |
| Q | Normalisation: no `<br>` on backspace, no block injection |
| R | Select-all includes chips (no `user-select:none`) |
| S | "Current value" and "Expected" layout (separate rows) |
| T | Data tab renders; collection pills have blue chip colours (skipped when no datasources) |

**E2E patterns for contenteditable formula input:**

```ts
// Clear the editor reliably (avoids keyboard interaction with chips)
await page.evaluate(() => {
  const el = document.querySelector('[data-testid="formula-input"]') as HTMLElement;
  el.innerHTML = '';
  el.dispatchEvent(new InputEvent('input', { bubbles: true }));
});
await page.waitForTimeout(600); // wait for 400ms debounce to push history

// Type into contenteditable to trigger auto-chip
await page.locator('[data-testid="formula-input"]').click();
await page.keyboard.type('(');
await page.waitForTimeout(200);
await expect(page.locator('[data-testid="formula-input"] [data-type="operator"][data-formula="("]')).toBeVisible();

// Paste a formula string with correct insert-form spacing (OP_TOKEN_RE requires spaces)
await page.evaluate(async () => { await navigator.clipboard.writeText(' >= '); });
await page.keyboard.press('Meta+v');

// Serialise editor to raw formula string
const formula = await page.evaluate(() => {
  const el = document.querySelector('[data-testid="formula-input"]') as HTMLElement;
  let out = '';
  for (const node of el.childNodes) {
    if (node.nodeType === Node.TEXT_NODE) out += (node.textContent ?? '').replace(/\u200b/g, '');
    else if ((node as HTMLElement).dataset?.formula) out += (node as HTMLElement).dataset.formula;
  }
  return out;
});
```

