## §39 Formula Editor — Tabs, Data Sections, Context, Variables, Quick Action

### Tab system

Four tabs exist; **Quick** only renders when the selected node is inside a repeated context:

| Tab ID | Icon | Label | Always shown? |
|---|---|---|---|
| `quick` | ⚡ | Quick | Only when inside a `map` ancestor |
| `variables` | `{x}` | Variables | Always |
| `data` | `≡` | Data | Always |
| `formulas` | `ƒ` | Formulas | Always |

**Tab order:** Quick (if visible) is always **first**. Remaining order: Variables → Data → Formulas.

**Default tab:** `'variables'` — the first tab is always selected when the formula editor opens.

**Auto-switch behaviour (implemented in `useEffect`):**
- When `isInsideRepeat` becomes `true` → switch to `'quick'`
- When `isInsideRepeat` becomes `false` and current tab is `'quick'` → fall back to `'variables'`

```ts
useEffect(() => {
  if (isInsideRepeat) setTab('quick');
  else if (tab === 'quick') setTab('variables');
}, [isInsideRepeat]); // eslint-disable-line react-hooks/exhaustive-deps
```

**Repeat detection:** `isInsideRepeat` walks the node tree upward from the selected node checking for any ancestor with a `map` property:
```ts
const isInsideRepeat = useMemo(() => {
  const id = selectedIds[0];
  if (!id) return false;
  let node = findNode(pageNodes, id);
  while (node) {
    if (node.map) return true;
    const parent = findParentNode(pageNodes, node.id ?? '');
    node = parent ?? null;
  }
  return false;
}, [selectedIds, pageNodes]);
```

---

### Section header styling (universal rule)

**All** section/category headers in the formula editor use:
- **Color:** `#e2e8f0` (near-white) — no accent colors on headers
- **Chevron:** `<FEChevron open={open} size={8} />` SVG arrow — never text `▾`/`▸`
- **Font:** `fontSize: 10, fontWeight: 600, letterSpacing: '0.05em'`

This applies to: Collections, Context, Pages, Colors, Typography, Border Radius (Data tab), all function categories (Formulas tab), and variable folder labels (Variables tab).

**Never use `textTransform: 'uppercase'`** on section labels — labels use title case (e.g. `Collections`, `Border Radius`, `From Project`).

---

### Function library categories

Keys in `FUNCTION_LIBRARY` use title case (not ALL CAPS):

| Key | Contents |
|---|---|
| `Conditional` | `if`, `ifEmpty`, `not`, `switch` |
| `Math` | `average`, `rollupSum`, `round`, `sum`, `toNumber` |
| `Array` | `add`, `contains`, `createArray`, `compare`, `distinct`, `filterByKey`, `findIndex`, … |
| `Object` | object utilities |
| `Text` | string utilities |
| `Utils` | general utilities |
| `Format` | `formatCurrency`, `formatDate`, `formatNumber` |
| `From Project` | dynamic — global formulas defined in this project |

The `'From Project'` literal key (used in the categorized render) must also match title case.

---

### Quick Action tab

Renders `<ItemContextGroup onInsert={insertChip} initialOpen={true} />` inside a scrollable container. The `initialOpen` prop:
- Sets `open` state to `true` on mount (item header expanded)
- Pre-populates `expanded` with `new Set(['data'])` so the `data` sub-tree is also open immediately

```ts
// In ItemContextGroup:
const [open, setOpen] = useState(initialOpen);
const [expanded, setExpanded] = useState<Set<string>>(
  () => initialOpen ? new Set(['data']) : new Set()
);
```

**Purpose:** Provides one-click access to all `context.item.data.*` fields without navigating Data → Context → item. The tree is fully expanded on open so data fields are immediately visible.

---

### `context.item` structure (weWeb format)

At runtime (`renderer.tsx`) and in the formula editor preview (`_formula-editor.tsx` `context` useMemo), `context.item` is structured as:

```ts
{
  // Spread of raw item fields for backward compatibility (e.g. context.item?.['slug'])
  ...rawItemFields,
  data: {
    ...rawItemFields,    // canonical path: context.item?.['data']?.['fieldName']
    index: 0,
    repeatIndex: 0,
    isACopy: false,
    parent: outerItemCtx | null,   // outer repeat's item context for nested repeats
    repeatedItems: arr,
  },
  // Top-level aliases for backward compat:
  parent: outerItemCtx | null,
  index: 0,
  repeatIndex: 0,
  isACopy: false,
  repeatedItems: arr,
}
```

**Canonical formula path:** `context.item?.['data']?.['fieldName']`
**Friendly label:** `item.data.fieldName`

All config JSON files must use `context.item.data.xxx` paths (not flat `context.item.xxx`). A migration script was run to update 146 references across 21 files.

`isScopeVariable` in `path-utils.ts` recognises all `context.*` paths:
```ts
path === 'context' || path.startsWith('context.')
```

---

### Theme chip categories and labels

Theme formulas use optional-chaining bracket notation: `theme?.['colors']?.['background']`

`CHIP_RE` matches all four categories: `colors`, `sections`, `fonts`, `radius`.

Display labels always include a category prefix:
- `Color - background`
- `Typography - heading`
- `Radius - sm`
- `Section - hero`

`populateEditor` strips the prefix before building the chip and re-adds it as the friendly label.

**Border radius:** `theme?.['radius']?.['sm']` resolves at runtime to `'rounded-sm'` via `THEME_OBJ.radius` map in `sdui-engine.tsx`.

---

### Variable chip color

`CHIP_STYLE.variable` uses teal (`#0f766e` bg, `#ccfbf1` text) — distinct from collection blue and context purple. Both the panel pill and the inserted formula chip use the same teal color.

**No `▣` or `ⓘ` icons** in `CollectionEntry`, `VariableEntry`, or `DataTreeNode` rows.

---

### Variables tab

Shows **only** user-defined variables from `config/variables.json`, grouped by folder. Folder labels use original casing (no `.toUpperCase()`).

`VariableEntry` mirrors `CollectionEntry` structure:
- Collapsible header with chevron + teal pill + live value display
- Expandable `DataTreeNode` for nested values
- Subscribes to `getGlobalVariableStore()` for live data

`VariableTree` subscribes to the global variable store so live data updates reflect immediately.

