## §50 Workflow Canvas — Dynamic SVG Line Geometry

All connector lines in `BranchNode`, `MultiOptionBranchNode`, and `LoopNode` must be measured at runtime. Never use static constants for SVG coordinates.

### Rule 1 — Use `ResizeObserver` for all geometry

Use `rowRef` on the columns container and `colRefs[i]` on each column `<div>`. Measure `offsetHeight`, `offsetWidth`, and offset position in a single `useEffect`:

```ts
const colRefs = useRef<(HTMLDivElement | null)[]>([]);
const rowRef = useRef<HTMLDivElement | null>(null);
const [layout, setLayout] = useState<{ xCenters: number[]; heights: number[]; rowW: number }>({
  xCenters: [], heights: [], rowW: totalW,
});

useEffect(() => {
  const measure = () => {
    const row = rowRef.current;
    if (!row) return;
    const xCenters = colRefs.current.map(el =>
      el ? (el.offsetLeft - row.offsetLeft) + el.offsetWidth / 2 : 0
    );
    const heights = colRefs.current.map(el => el?.offsetHeight ?? 0);
    setLayout({ xCenters, heights, rowW: row.offsetWidth });
  };
  const observers: ResizeObserver[] = [];
  [rowRef.current, ...colRefs.current].filter(Boolean).forEach(el => {
    const ro = new ResizeObserver(measure);
    ro.observe(el!);
    observers.push(ro);
  });
  measure();
  return () => observers.forEach(ro => ro.disconnect());
}, [/* allBranches.length for multi-option */]);
```

### Rule 2 — `offsetLeft` must be row-relative (critical for nested splits)

**Problem:** `el.offsetLeft` is relative to `offsetParent`, which bubbles up to the nearest positioned ancestor — the canvas `worldRef`. For nested splits, a column at local x=0 inside a parent column at x=608 has `offsetLeft=608`, placing SVG lines completely outside the SVG viewport.

**Fix:** Always subtract `row.offsetLeft` from every column's `offsetLeft`:

```ts
// ❌ BAD — relative to worldRef; breaks for any nested split
el.offsetLeft + el.offsetWidth / 2

// ✅ GOOD — relative to rowRef; correct at any nesting depth
(el.offsetLeft - row.offsetLeft) + el.offsetWidth / 2
```

### Rule 3 — Use `minWidth` not `width` on branch columns

**Problem:** `width: BRANCH_W` clamps the column — nested content (e.g. an inner 3-branch split = 876px) overflows invisibly and `offsetWidth` stays at `BRANCH_W`, producing wrong x-center calculations.

**Fix:** Use `minWidth: BRANCH_W` so the column expands to fit its widest child:

```ts
// ❌ BAD
style={{ display: 'flex', flexDirection: 'column', alignItems: 'center', width: BRANCH_W }}

// ✅ GOOD
style={{ display: 'flex', flexDirection: 'column', alignItems: 'center', minWidth: BRANCH_W }}
```

### Rule 4 — Loop container needs horizontal padding

**Problem:** `loopContainer` uses `alignItems: center`. When a nested `MultiOptionBranchNode` expands to fill the full width, the first and last column action cards touch the left/right dashed border of the loop.

**Fix:** Add horizontal padding to `loopContainer` so content is inset from the borders:

```ts
loopContainer: {
  // ...existing styles...
  paddingLeft: 24,
  paddingRight: 24,
}
```

### Rule 5 — LoopNode pill height is dynamic

The dashed border's top inset must match half the pill row height. Measure it with `ResizeObserver`:

```ts
const pillRowRef = useRef<HTMLDivElement | null>(null);
const [pillRowH, setPillRowH] = useState(34);

useEffect(() => {
  const el = pillRowRef.current;
  if (!el) return;
  const ro = new ResizeObserver(() => setPillRowH(el.offsetHeight));
  ro.observe(el);
  setPillRowH(el.offsetHeight);
  return () => ro.disconnect();
}, []);

// Use in the dashed border inset:
inset: `-${Math.round(pillRowH / 2)}px 50% 14px 0px`
```

