## §60 E2E Tests — Builder States (`e2e/builder-states-data.spec.ts`)

Tests for the StateBar and `_stateTag` system. All share a `sharedPage` with `beforeEach` reload guard.

| Test | ID | What it verifies |
|---|---|---|
| BSD-02 | Loading state | `_workflow.loading = true` injected into merged state |
| BSD-04 | Empty state | `activePreviewStates` contains `'empty'` |
| BSD-05 | Data state | `setCurrentPagePreviewData` stores data |
| BSD-10 | Single-select | Selecting a state replaces current; re-selecting reverts to `'normal'` |
| BSD-11 | All-pages state | Active and inactive pages share the same `activePreviewStates` |
| BSD-15 | `_stateTag` storage | `patchNodeField(id, '_stateTag', 'loading')` persists on node |
| BSD-16 | Loading isolation | Loading chip: loading-tagged node gets `_forceShowInEditor: true`; default-tagged gets `condition: false` |
| BSD-17 | Empty isolation | Empty chip: empty-tagged node gets `_forceShowInEditor: true`; default-tagged gets `condition: false` |
| BSD-18 | Custom tag badge | Custom tag stored; badge appears in layers panel |
| BSD-19 | Disabled overlay | Disabled chip adds `_forceDisabledInEditor: true` to nodes with `props.disabled` |
| BSD-20 | No global dim | Disabled chip does NOT add `opacity-50` to nodes without `props.disabled` |
| BSD-21 | No hover chip | `state-chip-hover` is absent from StateBar |
| BSD-22 | No error chip | `state-chip-error` is absent from StateBar |
| BSD-23 | Tag picker gating | `_stateTag` picker visible only when node has a `condition` set |

**Stability fix:** A `beforeEach` hook reloads the builder if the page URL has drifted (e.g. after a test failure that navigated away):
```ts
test.beforeEach(async () => {
  if (!sharedPage.url().includes('/dev/builder')) {
    await gotoBuilder(sharedPage);
  }
  await resetBuilder(sharedPage);
});
```
